    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/250</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 14, 3.24
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3344. Following is a summary of <hi rend="italic">communiqué</hi> issued by
                    German Legation 10th instant replying to Legation’s <hi rend="italic"
                        >communiqué</hi> concerning wheat shipments: <pb facs="0788" n="1622"
                        xml:id="pg_1622"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>American <hi rend="italic">communiqué</hi> indicates refusal of United
                            States to facilitate provisioning of Switzerland. Germany issued
                            immediate orders to naval forces to respect safe conducts, therefore the
                            American statement that Germany blockades Switzerland for three months
                            falsifies sense and meaning of German-Swiss agreement. America refuses
                            to adhere to facilities of transport consented to by Germany and exposes
                            transport of wheat to danger without any reason; briefly, America does
                            not wish to supply Switzerland.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>German <hi rend="italic">communiqué</hi> was very long and received scant
                    attention in Swiss press. <hi rend="italic">Journal de Genève</hi> says: “German
                    [omission] will not alter gratitude of Swiss people toward American Government.”
                        <hi rend="italic">Gazette de Lausanne</hi> points out that German Legation
                    seems to forget it is addressing a people endowed with some intelligence. <hi
                        rend="italic">Berner Bund</hi> believes in sincerity and good will of
                    American Government but feels submarine danger after German-Swiss agreement
                    reduced to negligible minimum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
